@startuml name "Refactor weakness - Rust command and import concentration"
title "Weak spot: Rust command facade and import normalization concentration"
rightfooter Conceptual zoom-in; Rust layer is modular, but some facades are still too broad

skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

skinparam component {
    BackgroundColor<<target>> #E8F5E9
    BorderColor<<target>> #2E7D32
    BackgroundColor<<crate>> #EDE7F6
    BorderColor<<crate>> #5E35B1
    BackgroundColor<<facade>> #FFF8E1
    BorderColor<<facade>> #F9A825
    BackgroundColor<<problem>> #FFEBEE
    BorderColor<<problem>> #C62828
    BackgroundColor<<fix>> #F1F8E9
    BorderColor<<fix>> #558B2F
}

legend right
  |= Marker |= Meaning |
  | <color:#2E7D32>green</color> | Intended command/capability split |
  | <color:#5E35B1>purple</color> | Rust capability crate |
  | <color:#F9A825>yellow</color> | Command facade / mixed transitional area |
  | <color:#C62828>red</color> | Responsibility concentration |
  | <color:#C62828>red dashed arrow</color> | Facade owns logic that should move behind service boundary |
  | <color:#558B2F>fix box</color> | Concrete remediation step |
endlegend

package "Concept target" {
    component "Tauri command registry\nthin command list or module registration" as TargetRegistry <<target>>
    component "Thin import command" as TargetImportCommand <<target>>
    component "Import service" as TargetImportService <<target>>
    component "Normalization / sanitization service" as TargetSanitizer <<target>>
    component "Storage service" as TargetStorage <<target>>
    component "Asset service" as TargetAssets <<target>>

    TargetRegistry -[#1565C0]-> TargetImportCommand
    TargetImportCommand -[#1565C0]-> TargetImportService
    TargetImportService -[#1565C0]-> TargetSanitizer
    TargetImportService -[#1565C0]-> TargetStorage
    TargetImportService -[#1565C0]-> TargetAssets
}

package "Actual weak spot in refactor" {
    component "[file]\nsrc-tauri/src/lib.rs\ncentral generate_handler!" as CommandRegistry <<facade>>

    package "src-tauri/src/commands/storage" {
        component "[file]\nimports.rs\nroutes, folder tokens,\nnormalizers, import writers" as ImportsRs <<problem>>
        component "[file]\nimports/bulk_imports.rs\nscan + run + progress" as BulkImports <<facade>>
        component "[file]\nshared.rs\nstorage normalization helpers" as StorageShared <<facade>>
        component "[group]\nprofile/assets legacy normalizers" as ProfileAssets <<facade>>
        component "[group]\nmedia/image/provider commands" as MediaCommands <<facade>>
    }

    package "src-tauri/crates" {
        component "[crate]\nstorage\nFileStorage" as RustStorage <<crate>>
        component "[crate]\nassets\nAssetService" as RustAssets <<crate>>
        component "[crate]\nsecurity\npath/name validation" as RustSecurity <<crate>>
        component "[crate]\nllm\nprovider transport" as RustLlm <<crate>>
        component "[crate]\nintegrations" as RustIntegrations <<crate>>
    }

    CommandRegistry -[#F9A825,dashed]-> CommandRegistry : every command registered in one list

    CommandRegistry --> ImportsRs
    CommandRegistry --> MediaCommands

    ImportsRs -[#C62828,dashed]-> ImportsRs : import routing + parsing + normalization\n+ persistence in one facade
    ImportsRs --> BulkImports
    ImportsRs --> StorageShared
    ImportsRs --> RustStorage
    ImportsRs --> RustAssets
    ImportsRs --> RustSecurity

    BulkImports -[#C62828,dashed]-> ImportsRs : calls shared import helpers\nfrom broad parent module
    StorageShared --> RustStorage
    ProfileAssets --> RustAssets
    ProfileAssets --> RustSecurity
    MediaCommands --> RustAssets
    MediaCommands --> RustLlm
    MediaCommands --> RustIntegrations
}

package "How to fix this weak spot" {
    component "1. Introduce focused import service\nImportService owns import workflows,\nnot the Tauri command file" as FixImportService <<fix>>
    component "2. Extract normalizers/sanitizers\nST character, lorebook, preset,\nMarinara envelope, profile assets" as FixNormalizers <<fix>>
    component "3. Keep commands thin\nparse request, validate command-level input,\ncall service, return DTO/event" as FixThinCommands <<fix>>
    component "4. Move service tests next to service\nnormalization, path safety,\nlegacy compatibility, id remapping" as FixTests <<fix>>
    component "5. Optional: command module registration\nEach command group exposes register_handlers()\nor a generated handler list per module" as FixRegistration <<fix>>
    component "Definition of done\nimports.rs no longer owns normalization + persistence.\nBulk import calls ImportService.\nCommand registry is mechanical, not architectural glue." as DoneRust <<fix>>

    FixImportService --> FixNormalizers
    FixNormalizers --> FixThinCommands
    FixThinCommands --> FixTests
    FixTests --> FixRegistration
    FixRegistration --> DoneRust
}

note right of ImportsRs
  This is the Rust analogue of a too-large module.
  It handles route dispatch, import payload parsing,
  SillyTavern normalization, Marinara envelope import,
  folder authorization tokens, image restore, and storage writes.
end note

note bottom of FixImportService
  The service can live in src-tauri/src first.
  It does not have to become a crate immediately.
  Promote it to a crate only when it has a stable public boundary.
end note

note bottom of FixNormalizers
  The original sketch's SanitizationModule maps here.
  It should be callable by single import, bulk import,
  profile import, and future import paths without duplicating rules.
end note

note bottom of FixThinCommands
  Thin command rule:
  no domain parsing loops, no large normalization functions,
  no multi-entity write workflow directly in command handlers.
end note

note bottom of RustStorage
  The crate split itself is healthy.
  The weak point is that some command facades still contain
  capability-level behavior instead of delegating to focused services.
end note

note bottom of CommandRegistry
  Monolithic command registration is not fatal,
  but it makes the host less module-owned than the original sketch implied.
end note

@enduml
